.TH MULTIFLEXI\-RUN\-TEMPLATE 1 "June 2026" "multiflexi-executor 1.16.0" "MultiFlexi"
.SH NAME
multiflexi\-run\-template \- run a MultiFlexi RunTemplate immediately
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B multiflexi\-run\-template
.B \-r
.I RUNTEMPLATE_ID
.RB [ \-o
.IR OUTPUT_FILE ]
.RB [ \-t
.IR SECONDS ]
.RB [ \-e
.IR ENV_FILE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B multiflexi\-run\-template
is a convenience alias for
.B multiflexi\-executor \-r
.IR RUNTEMPLATE_ID .
It creates a job record from the specified RunTemplate, queues it for
immediate execution and then blocks until the
.BR multiflexi-executor (8)
daemon has run it. Once the job finishes, its captured standard output is
written to stdout (or
.IR OUTPUT_FILE ),
its standard error is forwarded to stderr, and the command exits with the
job's own exit code.
.PP
The executor daemon must be running for the queued job to be picked up; if it
is not, the command waits until the timeout elapses (see
.BR \-t ).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-r " RUNTEMPLATE_ID" ", \-\-runtemplate=" RUNTEMPLATE_ID
Numeric RunTemplate ID to execute.
This option is required.
.TP
.BI \-o " FILE" ", \-\-output=" FILE
Redirect captured output to
.I FILE
(default: stdout or
.BR RESULT_FILE ).
.TP
.BI \-t " SECONDS" ", \-\-timeout=" SECONDS
Maximum time to wait for the daemon to execute the queued job.
.B 0
waits indefinitely
(default: 300, or
.BR RUNTEMPLATE_WAIT_TIMEOUT ).
.TP
.BI \-e " FILE" ", \-\-environment=" FILE
Path to the
.I .env
configuration file
(default:
.IR ../.env ).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
See
.BR multiflexi-executor (8)
for the full list of recognised environment variables.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Mirrors the exit code of the executed job process.
Exits
.B 124
if the timeout elapses before the daemon completes the job.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR multiflexi-executor (8),
.BR multiflexi-scheduler (8)
.SH AUTHOR
Vítězslav Dvořák <info@vitexsoftware.cz>
